gomodel:SYNGO_1797  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Both peak fluorescence and rate of synaptopHluorin re-uptake in Drp1 depleted cells were decreased when compared with scrambled shRNA controls (Fig. 5e). Drp1 depletion was rescued by overexpression of an shRNA-resistant Drp1 construct (Fig. 5f).\n\nDrp1-shRNA-expressing synapses showed multiple large vesicular structures (Fig. 7b). In addition, measurable synaptic vesicle area in electron micrographs of Drp1-depleted synapses was more variable and contained larger vesicles than controls (Fig. 7c).. Experimental description: From the methods, \"Primary rat hippocampal neurons were prepared as described previously...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1797" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

